4. Product Architecture

System Architecture Overview

EchoFinity is built on a modern, scalable microservices architecture designed to handle millions of concurrent users while maintaining high performance and reliability.

Architecture Layers:

Layer 1: Mobile Frontend (React Native) The mobile application is built with React Native, enabling a single codebase for both iOS and Android. This approach reduces development time, ensures consistency across platforms, and makes it easier to maintain and update features.

Layer 2: Backend API (Node.js + Express) The backend API handles user authentication, project management, token system, billing, and orchestration of AI and video processing services. Built with Node.js and Express for high performance and rapid development.

Layer 3: AI Processing Service (Python + FastAPI) Dedicated service for video analysis, scene detection, color grading suggestions, and other AI-powered features. Python is used for its rich ecosystem of AI/ML libraries.

Layer 4: Media Processing Service (FFmpeg + Node.js) Handles video encoding, transcoding, format conversion, and optimization. Uses FFmpeg for reliable, high-quality video processing.

Layer 5: Cloud Infrastructure (AWS) Leverages AWS services for scalability, reliability, and global reach: Lambda for serverless compute, S3 for storage, RDS for databases, CloudFront for content delivery, and SQS for job queuing.

Data Flow

Recording Workflow:

1.
User records video in mobile app

2.
Video is temporarily stored on device

3.
User initiates upload to cloud storage (S3)

4.
Backend creates project record in database

5.
Video is queued for AI analysis

AI Editing Workflow:

1.
AI service analyzes video (scene detection, audio analysis, color analysis)

2.
AI generates editing suggestions (cuts, transitions, color corrections)

3.
Suggestions are stored in database

4.
Mobile app displays suggestions to user

5.
User accepts, modifies, or rejects suggestions

Export Workflow:

1.
User selects export quality and format

2.
Backend checks user's token balance

3.
Video is queued for encoding

4.
FFmpeg encodes video at specified quality

5.
Encoded video is stored in S3

6.
User is notified and can download or share

Security & Privacy

Data Encryption: All data in transit is encrypted using TLS 1.3. Data at rest is encrypted using AES-256.

User Authentication: JWT-based authentication with refresh tokens. Users can authenticate via email, Google, or Apple ID.

Privacy: EchoFinity complies with GDPR, CCPA, and other privacy regulations. User data is never shared with third parties without explicit consent. Users can request data export or deletion at any time.

Content Moderation: Automated scanning for copyrighted music and inappropriate content. Users are warned before export if potential issues are detected.




